The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

                                        Archives
                                                   Ramiz view

           
	Karachi: Former Pakistan captain Ramiz Raja believes the ICC should appoint former players on senior positions to avoid a repeat of the Harbhajan Singh-Andrew Symonds row that severely damaged the games image. 
    
	Member boards need to have more faith and trust in the decisions taken by the ICC and its representatives and this can happen if more former players sit on the governing body, he said. (PTI) 
                                                   
